<document id="31628882"><sentence text="Interaction potential between clarithromycin and individual statins-A systematic review."><entity charOffset="30-44" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s1.e0" text="clarithromycin" /></sentence><sentence text="The high prevalence of statin and clarithromycin utilization creates potential for overlapping use"><entity charOffset="34-48" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s2.e0" text="clarithromycin" /></sentence><sentence text=" The objectives of this MiniReview were to investigate the evidence base for drug-drug interactions between clarithromycin and currently marketed statins and to present management strategies for these drug combinations"><entity charOffset="108-122" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s3.e0" text="clarithromycin" /></sentence><sentence text=" We conducted a systematic literature review following PRISMA guidelines with English language studies retrieved from PubMed and EMBASE (from inception through March 2019)" /><sentence text=" We included 29 articles (16 case reports, 5 observational, 5 clinical pharmacokinetic and 3 in vitro studies)" /><sentence text=" Based on mechanistic/clinical studies involving clarithromycin or the related macrolide erythromycin (both strong inhibitors of CYP3A4 and of hepatic statin uptake transporters OATP1B1 and OATP1B3), clarithromycin is expected to substantially increase systemic exposure to simvastatin and lovastatin (&gt;5-fold increase in area under the plasma concentration-time curve (AUC)), moderately increase AUCs of atorvastatin and pitavastatin (2- to 4-fold AUC increase) and slightly increase pravastatin exposure (≈2-fold AUC increase) while having little effect on fluvastatin or rosuvastatin"><entity charOffset="49-63" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s6.e0" text="clarithromycin" /><entity charOffset="200-214" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s6.e1" text="clarithromycin" /><entity charOffset="274-285" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s6.e2" text="simvastatin" /><entity charOffset="290-300" id="DDI-PubMed.31628882.s6.e3" te